<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,693,1979]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,322,1803,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[339,586,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Apolysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beijingensis">
<emphasis box="[339,586,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Apolysis beijingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali &amp; Evenhuis" authorityName="Gharali &amp; Evenhuis" box="[744,1157,1804,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Apolysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabrifrons">
<emphasis box="[744,909,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">A. glabrifrons</emphasis>
Gharali &amp; Evenhuis
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the following points: The 
<number box="[679,690,1841,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
st flagellomere is four times longer than wide; the knob of the haltere is milk-white; the epandrium is distinctly longer than high in the lateral view. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1181,1344,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Apolysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabrifrons">
<emphasis box="[1181,1344,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">A. glabrifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<number box="[1402,1413,1878,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
st flagellomere is twice longer than wide; the knob of the haltere is brown; the epandrium is as long as high in the lateral view (Gharali &amp; Evenhuis, in press).
</paragraph>
